<TITLE> Govt keen on birth registration </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 18 (bdnews24.com)  The government is set to launch a machine readable birth registration certificate scheme. It will also take initiatives to ensure registration within 45 days of birth. AKM Saiful Islam, project director of birth and death registration, said on Sunday that measures were on to make birth registration mandatory for all kinds of documents including national identity card, passport, and marriage registration. The project was recently extended to June 31 in its second phase. The Birth and Death Registration Law was formulated in 2004 and made effective in 2006. "Till 2005, the proportion of registered persons was 8.72 percent of the total population. It increased to 63.67 percent on Dec 31 2009," Saiful said. The project was 100 percent successful in eight districtsFeni, Noakhali, Rangpur, Magura, Nilphamari, Shariatpur, Khagrachhari and Norailtill date, he added. bd
